"On the scale of the nano-world, each of us is a universe that consists of perturbations of the wavy environment. Its elements structurally repeat each other up to a certain limit, until a change in values gives rise to a new property ..." — Spacelunch was enthusiastically introducing the scientific pop to his partner, who was a reputed lover of philosophical references to physics. Although such stories tended to reproduce themselves, this was an exceptional case — the entrance hall of the Biomolecular Institute of Venus served as a classroom, where many outstanding minds were schooled after the explosion of the Large Hadron Collider.

Climbing the enlarged DNA model as a library ladder, the professor thought about standards of different orders and the launch of an electromagnetic installation that allows reducing the size of objects by billions of times. With the installation of an artery in the background, Cat jumped from one erythrocyte to another, concentrating before each next manoeuvre. On the eve of crucial but dangerous tests, all interactions looked as relaxed as possible, but it was necessary to take all the risks into account.

Alternative uploading of scripts into the cerebral cortex has long been serving as a protection against the disastrous consequences of neurodegeneration. The sessions involve the introduction of updated software directly through the patient's energy field. During the Third Constellation War, the Smorings got the unspoken biohacking technologies from local looters who offered everything that came to hand.

— ...After all, I was a leading researcher of the observatory, and they treated me like this! Outrageous!
— Try to distract yourself, I need to connect to your nervous system. May the force of the elements be with us.

The Queen closed her eyes and gradually fell into a trance. A languid voice began to pronounce incantations in a strange language, to the beat of which Cat was snoring absently. The phrases resonated and stuck together. Healing psionic currents slid over Spacelunch's head, creating colored hyperspace kaleidoscopes in the darkness of his closed eyes.

"Hmm, the Voynich manuscript? The old man Bacon would be delighted right now...", — out-of-body experiences gradually subsided under dark glasses. A ringing silence hung around, which meant a complete shutdown of internal navigation. Failure to reinstall is fraught not only with disorientation, but also with the erasure of all skills. A few seconds remained to prevent the complete disintegration of the personality…

Episodes of sacred rites held near the bygone Indian reservation were emerging in Spacelunch's memory. According to the legend of the Sumerians, the sacred altar at the foot of the mountain of monuments hid the secrets of thousands of customs. Is it a lot or not? It is impossible to predict how the story could have continued if it had not been for the ritual with the potion made of the Ayahuasca.

The ceremony of reunion with the spirits of nature allowed barely noticeable sprouts to grow inside the consciousness — harbingers of a huge storm that knocks down and mercilessly shatters the mind like an empty bottle against stones. Defenceless humility and love in response to the laughter of the universe is the only chance to feel freedom, be alone with yourself and warm your neighbours with the inner fire.

The sabotage in the dungeons of a secluded flying prison is what really excites the mind. The deserters who committed a crime against the sound routine were detained here. A complex string of security cameras and fingerprint sensors left no choice. The access to the data library, which had been violently confiscated from prisoners, was only possible through a small window at the top of the dome.

 "Well, just a little bit more...", slightly biting his tongue to restrain the desire to rip the transparent armour open, Spacelunch filigreed his part of the work with a high-precision glass-cutter laser and a pair of suction cups. Drops of sweat traitorously rolled down his face, urging him to make it before the unintentional triggering of the security alarm.

The creaking of the bare cable on which Cat was descending was interrupted by loud thoughts about spys' failures and doubtless courage. The complex analysis of incoming information had a vulnerability – it reacted only to the smooth skin, so it turned out to be completely powerless in front of the agile, furry paws. Who knows what else will be found among the myriad of shelves, intriguing with their secrets…

Instantly, everything was covered with a veil of toxic fog. Suffocating fumes rolled into the respirators in dense corrosive clouds, which made it difficult for Cat to make out the readings of the holographic gas analyzer. The surface of the Mesozoic planet has an aggressive chemical composition, so finding a radioisotope generator stuck here is not an easy task.

Fortunately, a twilight pterosarius with an unusual structure of the respiratory system, who was tamed by Spacelunch in one of his travels, appeared out of nowhere. Its massive, webbed wings serve as the walls of a vacuum capsule, and its lungs, like a filter, create an atmosphere familiar to humans. The help turned out to be very useful. It's time to focus on the clicks of the dosimeter and detect the power source.

Bogged down in a pile of archival documents and adstracts from alchemical synopses, Spacelunch fell asleep unnoticed. Concentrated reading dragged him into the world of dreams which, as usual, was at his favorite desk. However, someone didn't want to stop there.

Naively inspired by the legend of homunculi, Cat decided to personally assess the activity of neurotransmitters in the ionized gas environment. The old experiments of their parasientific cooperation on the influence of information fields on the cerebral hemispheres were considered incomplete. Isn't this a reason for new experiments on the mental platform? As soon as the trial sample was subjected to intense exposure of the plasmaballs, tightly clamped in restless paws, there was a resounding click.

By chance, the professor's dream turned out to be less sensitive than it might seem at first glance. Jumping up after a piercing "meow", he felt the sharp smell of electrified wool: "Hey, buddy, are you okay?! Please be careful with the Tesla radiation!"

The painstaking preparation for the photon march took place in advance in chamber conditions. The seriousness of intentions was confirmed by loads of flasks, test tubes and neatly arranged reagents which require extreme concentration. The deductive-analytical board displayed a sequential chain of important events and complex chemical equations. The slightest oversight could lead to the disintegration of unstable elements.

Cat couldn't take his eyes out of the honed movements of the Spacelunch. In the minds of both flashed a whirlpool of thoughts, ranging from genetic engineering and varieties of crystal lattices, down to doubts and a desire to have a delicious dinner. A sleepless night in the mobile laboratory was supposed to bear fruit. However, to steal important data marked "secret", it will take much more time and effort than expected.

Making a loop around a cluster of yellow dwarfs, red giants and interstellar gas, the launched satellite returns to the Solar System once a year with a selection of the most important discoveries. On board is a traditional New Year's gift — a carefully assembled compilation of tracks from 2021.

We immensely appreciate the professionalism of the musicians and the dedication of everyone involved in the evolution of the project! Let the next earth cycle become the personification of love and care for everyone! The adventure continues!

The mysterious tracks led to the place where all the exoplanetary bohemians gathered. The signs, shimmering with multicolored diodes, rattled in unison with the rhythm of the dancefloor. The vibration seeped out from behind the doors and was noticeably felt in the chest area. The entrance to the club was securely guarded.

– Do you see this huge caterpillar? As soon as he turns away, I'll give the signal. Stay tuned.
– Yeah, they only serve in special detachments. On Alien-TV, they said that their hearing was not very good — Cat was in slight confusion and tried to calm himself with reasoning.
– We are waiting, a little more… Go ahead!

The surprise effect failed immediately after the astonished face of security appeared in the sights. Everyone froze, looking at each other in confusion.

– Hey, where are you going?
– Melvin...?! My friend, I can't believe my eyes!!! Who would have thought...
– You know. After leaving the Aerospace Corporation, I'm wary of harassment. And you, I see, obviously have not come to dance.
– Hats off, you're a master of conspiracy, but... We have almost fried you!

Melvin remained silent for a long time. The moment has come to reveal a lot of unexpected details.

Somewhere in the vicinity of Spaceport 15.

– You got so high last time, – Spacelunch said jokingly.
– Don't tell me, I thought the Minimal Antagonist was alive.
– Hush, fluffy, we should stay incognito at least until we meet with the informant. Don't jump to conclusions — I think that everything happened for a reason.

The streets of Chinatown attracted by the smells of exotic cuisine, what cannot be said about the sudden appearance of the detectives. Anyone who even occasionally felt the inquisitive eyes on them shied away from them. Sellers of all sorts of things were fussily whispering and continuously watching every step of the uninvited guests. The whole block seemed to know about the ongoing investigation. Looking around intently, the professor suddenly came across the strange but very familiar tracks.

"It can't be... the credentials and password turned out to be fake! Cat, follow me!" – Spacelunch made a note in his diary and walked rapidly along the stalls. He knew that the truth was somewhere nearby.

- What the hell is this...?!
- I... I don't know... Do you see it too?
- Believe it or not, I do see it! Well, get ready, you vile overgrown clam!!!
- Cat, remove the splitter, the gun won't help anymore...

The echoes of the past in the blink of an eye turned the feeling of slight confusion into a complete stupor. Gripped by the horror of the memories, the space stalkers froze in front of a black mass with nasty, slimy hanging tentacles. The growing confusion was completely ingrained in their minds and was becoming more pronounced by the minute.

Sticky tar-like drops were falling loudly from the ceiling. It was as if someone had turned off the light and shuffled the measurement deck overnight. The despair reached its climax when hundreds of blade-sharp suckers hung down at arm's length. Death agony or last chance?

- Hey... Do you hear me? We need an antidote! - Spacelunch moved abruptly.
- It was an honor for me to fight side by side with such an amazing partner...
- Damn it, I'll try to free my hands.

Sometimes desperate adventures tend to come to an end. Apparently, one of them is closer to the completion than ever...

The path to the sacred altar at the foot of the mountain of Monuments wound through the ruins of the Dead City that resembled an ancient Phoenician settlement. There was only one thing that was alarming here — strong landscape distortions. The web of streets and blocks weaved endless patterns, rounding the corners and drawing strange, sometimes impossible geometry. Dilapidated palace towers with mysterious frescoes and time-worn colonnades reminded of a once prosperous state. The smell of decay and the cold shade of the fortress walls reminded of the times of padishahs and sultans who greedily fought for the throne.

- What are you thinking about all the time?! - Spacelunch exclaimed nervously, anticipating the answer in advance.
- Well, do you remember the last time something like this happened and...
The professor cut him off in disgust:
- Come on, it's all over with him!
- To find a way out, we must activate mechanisms that change the route, - Cat immediately noticed.
- But this is possible only with the help of the hectopod – the totem of optical illusions, you know?

"A shock dose of tranquilizers will allow you to maintain concentration for some time," Spacelunch said carefully, "the most terrible thing in this situation will be the loss of sanity. The tides of the Green Moon cause the strongest hallucinations when influencing the hypotolamus."

The music led the inexorable hunters with an invisible hand, balancing in each the beginning and the end, the twilight of the shadow side of the moon and the energy of solar flares — Yin and Yang. The poisonous formaldehyde cloud began to dissipate. Cat cast a confused glance at the body, which was no longer the same, but still obeyed him...

"Damn it, we succeeded! Superpower has been studied!" SpaceCat exclaimed enthusiastically. The mission revolved around a simple truth: to see one part of yourself, you need to see the other, which means that only harmony and balance open up new trajectories in the knowledge of space.

Having successfully requested a landing on one of the orbits of Alpha Centauri, the adventure hunters set a course for the Smoring Valley. This friendly people had been under the yoke of the invaders for many years, until the rebel movement was led by their Queen – the guardian of the elements.

Skirting the dunes with the rusted remains of launch vehicles, the whirlwinds of a psychokinetic storm and radioactive swamps, the exhausting road ran to the foot of the lighthouse.

– It's not safe to come around here right now, but I know what you're looking for. Follow the tides of the Green Moon.

«Not this one...», – Spacelunch realized how high a price he would have to pay for the Seer amulet.

The bustling activity of the Earth colonizers had long since died out, so no one could be found on the deserted streets of «Spaceport 15» except astromechanical droids – local law enforcement officers. Spacelunch was looking for something special here, rather than an answer to another puzzle.

By mixing the serum reagents to study the space-time continuum, the professor hoped to gain access to the primordial hearth and reassign internal directives. After taking the right dosage, he habitually looked at his partner and, barely uttering a word, felt a soft isoteric glow.

– The chosen path is not accidental, my friend.
– Cat? Did you just say that?!
– The universe will take care of everything, just listen to yourself...

The flagship's command console was filled with a myriad of controls, buttons and sensors. It was time to get out of the cyberdemon lair. The incomprehensible digital ratios seemed a strange rebus, even for experienced intergalactic wanderers. The stormtrooper squad was already on the way, so all the modulations were done intuitively.

Suddenly, Cat felt something irresistible, not limited by the laws of physics. A surge of energy forced his body to move to the rhythm of the sound-pumping speakers. "Mechatronics!" said Spacelunch with a grin. He had guessed the existence of such engineering solutions. At the right moment, the once-tamed element helped launch the plasma engines. It was enough to rely on hearing.

Aloha!
Mike Schommer's musical expression formed the basis of the plot of his new record. A deliciously unsettling ode to the '90s subculture in Port Huron (Michigan), demonstrates the eccentricity and inspirational influence exerted on the American master over the past few decades.
The author's counterform subverts the orthodox approach and genre claims. Fitting in the right proportions in a cognitive audio performance, remixes accompany fairy-tale originals and develop mediated audio discourse. The colorful music library is complemented by the diligent, overflowing radiance of the southern chronicler Artur Galstyan aka Heavenchord, the traditionally fresh, exciting delights of Peter Fanai and the ornate frescoes of the Echoton brothers.
The multi-part exhibition invites you to the publishing house "spclnch". Welcome to the world of sincere thoughts, monumentalism and borderline stylizations with a share of curiosities!

After bypassing the security system and gaining access to the classified archives of the aerospace corporation, Spacelunch discovered something important – the protocols of closed photon tests. The atavistic horror he had experienced in the depths of the infernal dimension only encouraged him to master psychotronic cryokinesis.

It was necessary to derive the formula for the collapse of the dark galactic stratum as soon as possible. This process will lead to a powerful flash and the release of energy of the giant cooling rings, which will put an end to the chilling experiments on consciousness.

Unearthing the ruins of a vanished Martian civilization has led to a portal to an apocalyptic, aggressive world, where the echoes of race battles thundered, flames blazed everywhere and demonic priests pestered. The previous research team left behind only SOS signals, frightening with their helplessness and encrypted on the flight recorder as a warning to all outsiders about the inadmissibility of staying here.

The audio messages contain information about strange pataphysical phenomena, suspicious accidents, and a mass obsession of the expedition members. Rare specimens of the fauna of the infernal dimension, collected at the cost of many human lives, pointed to the main mystery – a sarcophagus with ancient writings sealed with an occult pentagram. The die is cast, what remains is being patient and count on luck.

After passing through the sights of the clouds of galactic dust, the patrol cruiser brought the brave, hard-to-get-out-of-trouble friends to the Andromeda Nebula. An astrophysical textbook with the basics of meta-cognitive therapy is of a great help in planning new searches in the depths of the celestial web, reboot and dream circulation.

Cat performs a ritual of debugging vibration fields with the help of immersive mantras. Their light, airy reflections have long been used to eliminate nonverbal attacks on consciousness. The multidimensional immersion in the cradle of sound sensorics becomes tangible.

Bingo! The encounter with the minimal antagonist, who was following the irreconcilable ufologists during the quantum leap, was so unexpected that they barely realized how they switched bodies.

The endless maze of stairs and abandoned, winding corridors of the aerospace corporation was confusing due to spatial reversion. The cuttlefish's minions, the shadow phantoms, followed them step by step like its ubiquitous giant tentacles, crawling underfoot and along the walls.

Cat 007 fastidiously refused to put up with the role of prisoners and, grabbing his friend, blasting well-aimed, cutting shots from the service blaster, left a couple of decent holes in the energy field of annoying creatures. Without a doubt, it became obvious that interplanetary explorers were being hunted.

They didn't come here for nothing. Spacelunch was promising the merge with energy-informational thinking substances at the level of elementary particles. The crystal sound spread like ectoplasm along the walls of the reflecting vessel of the universe. Drama and the eager grin of adventure have slowed down, bowing its heads in submission to the convergence of musical exuberance. Meditation on the event horizon lit the torch of sharpened perception of all the amplitude shifts.

Dubby substrate absorbed every scrap of the all-pervading ether. This meant that the indefatigable pioneers had harnessed the elements, becoming the bearers of important, extracted knowledge. From now on, their bioresonators are as precisely tuned as possible to the condensation of acoustic waves, which, like a compass, will point the way to the probabilities that emit a powerful impulse. Space stalking and audio transcription are being taken to the new dimensions.

Having won approval and success in its debut release, the spclnch vinyl series continues with the release of a second record from Wiesbaden producer – Peter Fanai.
Weighty, spacious bass pleiades fill the sound field, erase the consequences of duality and, flowing into the viscous full-bodied substance of verified sound design, it would seem that they will momentarily shift the tectonic plates of the electronic genre.
Maestro Basicnoise is again involved in the spatial enrichment of textural proportions of reverberation and percussion. This time, their sequence runs under the quality mark of the Australian-German collaboration. The accurate Kooscha warms up the sensorics with elegant dance manipulations and a distinct rhythm, and the related association Echoton traditionally introduces a tart concentrate of meaningful thoughts.
The rich aftertaste of variable electronic abstractions takes the subconscious and musical outlook to a different plane.
Now you are more than an observer.

A beam of intense light drew the professor's attention to the hypno-spiral, which had become his first goal in studying astronomical objects of the "Quasar" class. However, everyone has their own desires. Cat, for example, tried to comprehend passionarity and look at the reflection of what was happening. The genre scenes that unfolded before the eyes of the experimenters went beyond the 3d dimension. Bubble pattern, cold draft, rusted house, wet format – they seemed to be on the verge of insanity.

Although in the past the Spacelunch studied at the Department of Experimental Phonetics and Speech Synthesis, the adaptation of consciousness was still difficult. The answers to the inner questions turned into a swarm of sound isotopes. Space was shifting, going deep, rotating and stretching in all possible directions, reducing all efforts to concentrate almost to zero. No wonder, because music is not just a technical object, but an ideological principle. The delta dimension, which is full of spectral lines, is clearly not the place for a logical routine with complex calculations - the auditory stream expresses something more, just trust the sensations.

By tradition, spclnch is proud to present a very special collection of carefully selected and compiled tracks for 2020. This is a small gift for all the listeners who support us on our journey. Let's continue to spread love together.

Thank you to all our incredible producers and all the people who make the label what it is.

After a decent corpuscular thrashing, the calibration of the control systems went in normal mode.
When the readings of the instrument were analysed, there was an enthusiastic voice on board: "Thermoregulation is normal, cap! Electromagnetic induction and differential change of the phase integral are calculated! Full speed ahead!"

After passing through the dense asteroid belt, the broken testers found that a kinetic teleport spat out their aircraft near the orbital station "Research Institute of Cybernetics", where an unscheduled study of the dynamic modulations and illumination of the moon was carried out using ultrasonic transducers.

With amazing ease, they ended up in the center of scientific research, in the middle of a landfill filled with splitting blasters and life-size holographic models. The mechanics of this action had an absolutely mesmerizing effect, making anyone who witnessed it freeze in amazement. The slow-motion fashion show of the prototypes reflected the metamorphoses of the growing (as they say among Earthlings), full and waning moon, reminding us of the grandiosity of the internal changes of each of us and of the magnetic integrity they possess.

It's hard to imagine how even experienced adventurers envied these travellers, bound by an invisible, strong thread of excitement for discovery. But what will they become: a collection of fears and questions or the embodiment of a real experience? The cabin shook, the sensors screeched in unison, announcing extreme overload, a bright flash! Emptiness. What is it: strange whispers, snatches of sounds, noises, echoes of the frightening unknown rang in my ears.

It soon turned out that riding the waves of atomic-molecular flow is not so scary. Quantum teleportation is quite a common process for those who have fallen into the cold embrace of a black hole. Random formulas, geometric progressions, and a detailed model of the universe pop up in your mind as if at someone's command. Suddenly, a strange silhouette flashed past - perhaps a clot of dark matter, or perhaps someone got caught in an endless cycle and rushed with great speed into a parallel dimension. The main thing is not to break into particles from such a swirl and strong rotation.

The intergalactic tornado calmed down and the image stabilized. Just think, until recently Cat could not imagine such a story. His eyes widened in surprise. Looking at each other, the friends realized that everything had happened for a reason, they were being watched...

The alien scenario was unfolding very dynamically, so the daring pilgrims decided to look into one quaint place where you can hide from the universal bustle, take a breath and enjoy the spatial modeling. By the way, it helps to recover after critical overloads through fine motor skills.

Welcome to the heavenly body "Orlan 19". Once it was assigned an ordinal number, and it got this name because of its ultra-low gravity. Obviously, this "dwarf" became an attraction and just a recreational area for many nomads. Its atmosphere is literally packed with thoughtfully hovering objects of various configurations. A kind of metaphysical equilibrium. Here it is customary to not only enjoy the abundance of entertainment, but also the thoughts about where the consciousness leads us in search of its home.

Deftly juggling patterns, the technologist grabbed an experimental sample labeled RTW1350, which, thanks to its composition and consistency, easily gives the appearance of a basketball.
Catch - the next throw is yours!

Due to the impact, the spaceship's landing struts dug into the hard surface, forming a dense dust cloud around them. They departed too far from their intended trajectory and made a forced hard landing. A critical dose of meteor fragments damaged one of the engines. It was necessary to fix the damage as soon as possible or to get an alternative type of fuel.

After looking around them, the space travelers began to move towards the mysterious craters almost by feel. Suddenly, the ground got out from under their feet. Due to poor visibility, the rush led to an expectable outcome. "Great, we're trapped!", - Cat looked at his companion from under his brows, insistently hinting at a clear explanation of what was happening.

– This is a Planet of Mineralization's Dubs, my friend.
– Hm...
– Its interior consists of metamorphic deposits formed by layers of two types of fossils: igneous and sedimentary.
– Mineralization's Dubs?!
– I don't know, what's bothering you?
– At least the fact that we are waist-deep in a swamp with an incomprehensible viscous substance!
– We'll get out, don't doubt it. There are still many mysteries to solve in the Universe. Just focus on these sound waves, can you hear them?

The long-standing dispute has still persisted, fueling the excessive interest in finding the artifact in the minds of avid friends. It's time to start exploring the sky and the blurry, bright streaks of constellations passing by.

Cat’s partner's habit of putting his feet up on the spaceship's dashboard has sometimes disturbed him, but it hasn't stopped him from briskly sorting through the options in their traditional “Last Letter” game, where words denoted instances of sound, time, and space, rather than the usual Earth cities.

A long journey is coming and it is unknown which form of matter will be encountered this time.

Is that real that the Solar System looks different from Saturn... Possibly the reason of distortion is light refraction in gravitational field. But why then we don't feel it? Are we really able to feel the moment's flow in space?

It's hardly possible that Cat could think about this kind of stuff during his tries in simple exercises for balancing without inherent grace. So, what is it? Elevation or just weightless...

One thing is for sure - the only gravitational pull between them is music that brought so far.

Spacelunch and his loyal friend Cat are thousands of light-years away from the galaxy they once thought was their own. Obsessed with the thirst for discoveries of the depths of extraterrestrial civilizations, they are wandering in search of unexplained phenomena from different worlds.

Looking back to their roots, space collectors want to get a different view of the origin of the universe. Although it was impossible to say exactly in what dimension their story began, all these journeys have made sense just now.

The suborbital German brotherhood Echoton, united by free creative intelligence and mutual expansion of the musical range, deciphers the mystery of the mind machine.
Detail-organic, avalanche-like electroacoustics of Alexander and Michael rushes to the top of the console futurism. The flow of sound, though not always obvious, manipulations creates a sense of dynamic balance.
The incomprehensibly abstract environment, saturated with biology and meaning of digital structures, finds its culmination in a Remix from the master of uncompromising grooves — Basicnoise! His boundless space Odysseys are echoed by a deep bass that abolishes ephemeral musical constructions.

When it comes to a starship, it often seems to be something huge. However, once it comes closer to the Saturn, giant size of the interstellar vehicle turns to atomic particles. Great shadow of the planet envelops spaceship making it transparent in total darkness, like immersing it to the chambers of depression, so cold and distant.
The mind falls down to infinity when faced with thousand years objects. Probably, living beings will never understand what does it feel like a hundred million years long life travelling through endless empty space.

The Universe possibly wouldn't have any sense if the space wasn't permeated by stardust. Its particles are in motion for millions of years conceiving nebulas, star systems and galaxies which are eventually going to return to their initial state.
Everything around is weaved from the same star matter, first creating and then destroying. And everything cycles and repeats again and again.
This is the inevitability, the law of existence.
We only get to observe.

If only we could go back to childhood…
Just for a moment take a look at yourself so small through the window of your house.
What makes this little human happy? There is nothing better than feeling that the most important people are here, right next to you. At this touching moment there happens divine miracle - Love.
Have things really changed since then? Maybe.
However something has remained unchanged and comes to visit us occasionally - it's a belief in goodness, something that we have from the very beginning.
This is our little secret out of time.
The main thing - to trust in that.

Life is nothing but illustrated collection of stories that naturally updates itself. Often it happens quietly and only some time after it can be found that compilation has become thicker and brighter.

Everything changes, but not immediately. Conditions, distances…
Whether it is red sunset going below the horizon, or whether it is space satellite flight so far from the visible area.
Only later changes impact can be observed. Most often it is achieved by little but daily work. This is the way how stars are forming and planets are moving. The difference is how much time does it need to see the tangible result.

Sweet sorrow or absolute happiness can knock on our door with the album of memories. Nobody will ask us do we need that right now or not - the injection of nostalgia takes the effect of tranquilizer in order to let us see the world in which we had been living some time ago.

Fairy tales from past remind us about the events that were happening so long time ago. Later, even not the most pleasant memories somehow are wrapped in serene foil forming the integrated whole in the lifestream.

Every creation has its creator, however, we concentrate on different colors of events once we encounter with art.
But does the artist really match with the messages he reflects in his work? What if not?
One could be deeply disappointed due to ones high expectations. Art can be referred to some ideals, while people are never perfect.

It is our nature to chart dividing lines in order to adjust everything around us. There is a reason because everybody has their own limits. To define boundaries, to make laws and establish the rules of the game - that is so like to the way we go.
Possibly, it is necessary need to define ourselves as independent entity and make scope of allowable things.
That’s why we are so different.
That’s why we are so similar.

spclnch proudly presents a very special collection of carefully selected and compiled tracks for 2019. This is a small gift for all the listeners who support us on our journey. Let's spread love together.

Contact
Get ready and take the seatbelt off.
No, this is not because of the danger that has passed. Rather it is in order to rein in the weightlessness.
Who says that the Contact is going to take place in our natural environment? We will try to be ready for that.
The unknown frightens and at the same time it envelops with attempts to find out what is that.
However, we are going to learn for sure who or what we are dealing with, as it is inevitable. So take it slow because there is a little eternity to spare.

Endless space of the Universe help us when we want to disappear completely. At this moment it seem to be like only open space can give us feeling of safety when there is nothing and nobody but you. Vacuum.
But what if we seriously imagine that we have an opportunity to be all alone among endless space… Will we be in safety for real? Do we exist?
Maybe we are nothing but the product of our own imagination and there is nothing around in the reality?
Just mysterious emptiness and fear.

So this is the limit.
Energy flow inside has reached a critical point. There is just one moment before the explosion - when the Universe arrives at a balance. This feeling is like a full of resolving but unconscious and spontaneous.
Explosion is natural need in order to give birth to something new and powerful. Like a bolt of lightning during the storm, energy flows will come out with its deadly power.
Quiet tension, just calm before the storm - this exact point of fragile balance. Just one thing is inevitable - energy flow will come out.

Three dub Musketeers, nobly animating the ubiquitous flow of reverberations, skillfully fence with micro-textures. Desolated melancholy and dotted rhythm emphasize the formlessness of ambient structures, causing emotional restraint.
The limited edition record by Vincent Raude (Upwellings), a French cultivator of deep-sea dub techno streams, comes from the bowels of analog synthesizers. Its sound makes sense and steadily penetrates into the auditory range, expressing the interactive-spatial evolution of music.
Peter Fanai (Basicnoise), a lover of subtle dubby jams, producing from late 90s and consistent, methodical electronic pedant from Sydney Kyryl Polozyuk (Kooscha) made a vinyl contribution.

«Once you have chosen your path, you will become it. The once perplexing vicissitudes of fate will be taken as a starting point. We are here and continue to see incredible in the usual!»

You're standing on a cold iron beam and you can't believe your eyes. You see only stars, nebulae and total darkness. Concentration is more important now than ever before, otherwise there is a risk of falling and dissolving into infinite space. But what is it around? Space? Another dimension? Or maybe it's a tunnel full of your fears and memories?
Yeah, we all have something to hide, and you're not an exception. You can run as fast as you can, at light speed, but remember, you can't run away from yourself.
It's all about what's between the lines of yourself.
It seems like you're stuck here in the middle of your fear cosmos forever. And you know what? It's the truth. Your thoughts will find you. Wherever you're hiding, wherever you're trying to go.
Those distant stars, that frightening darkness... That's all is you.
Now you understand: there is only one way - to move forward.

Your internal world is your abode. These endless corridors are like the nooks and crannies of the megapolis that hides a lot of mysteries.
Where the boundaries of the inner world end, there begins secret and the multifaceted external world with its unstable atmosphere and stories. These worlds have no clearly defined framework, and one hardly can exist without the other one. Only plunging into the outside world, only hiding in the unknown space, you can extend the territory of your own megapolis.
Returning to your domain, take a look around, because the avenue of your consciousness has already expanded.

Nowadays, the energy of life pulsates to such an extent that tranquility has become a luxury.
Ask yourself: how often are you in a state of peace and harmony with yourself? Perhaps you should relax and finally open your eyes?
We have what you need for that.

A portion of minimalism, glitch and all sorts of digital artifacts from Drifted, complete with remixes from Echoton and Asvajit.

Wait stranger, take a look around.
Have you ever noticed how many things are happening around, that everything has its own rhythm, its sense of time and space. And all about that is interconnected. Time... It's what points the way, making you different from whom you were a moment ago. It is worth remembering, it flows in only one direction, and therefore causes such a strong interest.
Let the rhythm of time pass through you and give it free rein. And then it becomes clear that the present moment is something elusive. This is the moment when emotions, events and space merge together, when you catch yourself of thinking that the moment you are living is eternal. But only here and only now.
If you could choose which moment to pause and make it last forever, which one it would be?

In the compilation, the theme of time was used as a foundation. Each participant revealed it in its own way, original and unique. Each of them knows exactly how to stop time and grasp the moment of eternity. Pleasant journey.

Continuation can be found on hello▼strange:
hellostrange.bandcamp.com/album/time

Any journey is nothing but a set of transitions: from one point to the second, from one state to another. People like to travel, even if they do not move at all.
We suggest you hold your breath and dive. Don't be afraid. There is only one condition: trust!

They say that only flowers live for real. Live their allotted days so desperately flowering that they know better than people of the transience of life.
Romance, magic, goodness, beauty and true love - listening to such music, we water the flowers that grow in us.
Pleasant listening.

spclnch presents the first release from Australian producer and DJ Kooscha called «Reflections».
Everyone is inclined to see their own reflections in the world. After all, they are a logical continuation of us. Carefully, leisurely, calmly and harmoniously, sometimes hypnotizing, the author moves us from composition to composition, then picking up the pace, then slowing down, leaving a pleasant aftertaste. Enjoy listening!

podcasts.description: The basic noise comes from the citadel of scientific disciplines. The square near the Department of Machine Learning and Data Analysis is packed — the crowds of extragalactic races have surrounded the source of attractive meta-vibrations. The maestro is controlling the decks, ignoring the flotilla of patrol flying saucers and the pile of casemates. A top-secret location based dozens of astronomical units from the Sun turns into the epicenter of pleasure. The educational mission is gaining momentum thanks to the assistance of BDTom, Nicholas Barnes and Schulz Audio.

The campus of the Biomolecular Institute of Venus is full of surprises and is designed for curious adepts. This proposed audio lecture is conducted by the adviser of the educational cluster – Thomas Carmody from the planet 70P. The programme of the performance includes the stimulation of neurotransmitters using digital procedures.

Visual aid for shifting perspectives and increasing the auditory range helps relieve the stress and relax. The scientific dissertation consists entirely of the developments of honorary graduates, including Pachh, Versa and Krissky. The number of seats is not limited.

Artificial light is entangling with woodlands of lianas and broadleaved thickets. The space is filled with green essence, and the chirping of insects is beating an energetic pace that leads to dizziness. Condensation is running down the glass walls, attracting curious glances from passers-by outside. When the viscous fog clears, the caretaker of the Museum of Living Fossils, Dave Stuart, shows off his collection: author's exhibits by Quantec, Tm Shuffle and Alessandro Crimi.

An hour and a half tour of the Earth Museum ended in a miniature of the black-and-white light district, pulsating with a ridge of gingerbread houses. A hauntology-like cast of the former vital activity was restored remotely using ultrasonic blasters. Reconstructors Luna Ludmila, Roger Gerressen and Anton Kubikov transform the data, creating multifactorial prototypes of the Old World cities.

The orbital climatron which contains the relict flora from the past plant epochs is the clearest demonstration of evolutionary diversity. In the cascade of appearances, the intonations of the magnolia greenhouse are easily recognized, sounding with all sorts of timbres and phonetic phenomena. A live beat of creative interfaces permeates everywhere, adjusting the frequency of signal during the synaptic transmission. Steve O'Sullivan, Sven Weisemann and Grad_U are studying new hybrid compounds as part of the botanical expertise.

The beta testing of mechanical amplitudes on the ISS went smoothly and lasted about an hour. Weightlessness has long been familiar, but the influence of nootropic noise components is a novelty for astronauts. The portholes of the main module contain enough fragments for the synesthesia training and well-coordinated interaction of the crew members: Ohrwert, Ohm & Octal Industries and Dan Goul.

3, 2, 1... Cheese! Mobile engineering solutions captured the second season of a large-scale odyssey (SL30–SL39). The telescopes are already tuned to maximum clarity for the sustained perception of the neurophysical system. Voice-over explanations will help to see the sound nanostructures in detail.

Kyryl Polozyuk knows firsthand about the secrets of the Martian caves which have amazing acoustics due to their impressive size and many giant stalactites. The eternal silence is occasionally broken by the melodious roll call of basalt columns, the rustle of burning primus or the rhythmic noise of oxygen cylinders.

Music is in everything. Malin Genie, Per Hammar and Silverlining are dissecting the excitations of infrasound waves as part of a planetary expedition.

Many spatial sectors are closed in a time loop which is conducting the search of ideal proportions from the beginning of times. Whether it is the works on ancient geometry or a treatise on the golden ratio, everything in the universe is infinitely striving for harmony.

The genius of the Etruscan engineering and the Aztec masonry is integrated into the multilevel optimization of Giriu Dvasios. The depicted object is divided into simple elements and reconstructed in a new guise. Greetings from Orlan 19 from the musical designers: Slownoise, Paolo Lucchi, Joergmueller.

Having traveled millions of light-years, Topology's analog configurations flicker far beyond the Milky Way. In a secluded place in the middle of a cold relic spot, the uniform flow of drums falls in time with the natural algorithms of the body. Spontaneous introspections of Barac, Zefzeed and Dubfound open free access to the intergalactic pool party. Welcome!

The gravitational slingshot has delivered the manned probe "Ekstendia" to the interstellar electron cloud. The analysis systems are recording a veil of moderate, rhythmic vibrations near the entrance to the Wormhole.

Flowing in a relaxed way between the points of perception and physical states, the auditory flow is built by Nicolas Barnes, Raytek and Schulz Audio. The saturated spectral composition activates the plasticity of dance and neural network effects.

The inaccessible slopes have long been familiar with the spontaneous echo flooding a huge network of exoplanetary gorges. No wonder, as this is dub.

Padawan Alexey Filin has long been a master of the DP-6 Order. Taming the natural call of music, he makes a steep ascent to the observation deck of the neurophysical system. From here, a new cycle of the generation of sound constellations is clearly visible. The senses recognize and absorb their essence thanks to the guides of the world of electronic processes — Upwellings, Traumer and Ludowick.

In an underwater odyssey through the depths of the microcosm, Thomas Carmody is bound to look around more than once. Many rare species and supernatural phenomena coexist without any conflict in the turbulent flow of music.

Does the immersion remain an accident, or are these decorations skillfully arranged by the Creator, peeping with delicate curiosity? Maybe our world is not a huge quantum ocean at all, but just a small aquarium?

The employees of the hydrophysical division: Dubonautik, Subset and Ikosaeder descend into the abyss on a swift bathyscaphe to scan the level of 60 leagues with dub-sounders.

Giacomo Pellegrino's magical psilocybin forest whispers stories that are too tempting to pass by. An oasis in the middle of a cold space wilderness meets with a pleasant disorientation and weightlessness.

An hour surrounded by percussive cicadas and firefly pads is enough for maximum exacerbation of the auditory receptors. Here, on the fluorescent edge, the Auckland brothers Chaos In The CBD, abbots Luke Hess and Federsen, prepare their potions. The exploration of parallel worlds is in full swing!

The angry compilation originates in the heart of the alien mind, intending to give birth to a race of a higher order. To create a private code, Bruit Blanc uses acoustic greetings from extraterrestrial civilizations. The encrypted methods of Zaur Pseush, Lyosha Bolgarin, Vadim Indigo and Alexey Filin set a mercurial movement and a somewhat provocative character of the dub-almanac.

Finally, Tom Larson had a chance to visit the planet of dub-mineralization together with a research group. Little has changed here since then. Pulling the space apart with viscous rhythmic textures, he creates a prototype of an open universe with the help of exaflop calculations. The sound analysis indicators were noted by Christoph Schindling, Altone and Frank Hellmond in the laboratory journal under item 57.

The commander of the Starship Troopers squad, Roman Airkey, is storming the ruthless, giant jaws of silence with a parascientific dub-annihilator. Entering into a desperate battle, he manages to capture the repeater. The chilling, cave mix is decorated with clever maneuvers by experienced scouts — Mikael Delta, Octal Industries & Ohm.

Two fives in the corner of the touch console show the assigned course with bright red winks. A slight roll and tonal signals notify about the docking with the "YINYANG" unmanned storage facility.

M-Eject came here to extract the structures of ancient DNA. Meanwhile, his assistants Basicnoise, Kooscha and Ohrwert are experimenting with molecular acoustics, feeling the gazes from the depths of the galaxy on themselves.

True seekers rely on good intuition. Why not demonstrate it? Hannes Salvers has prepared an elegant turntable guest mix, exuding a pleasant shimmer in the firmament of sounds. The space shuttle will deliver signals from different constellations to your ears — among them musical messages from Mikhail Vityuk, Scott Monteith, Harvey Jones and Koos Ludwig.

We are pleased to welcome our friend from Florence Leonardo Patrizi (Dott. Santafeo) with such a wonderful musical selection from his personal vinyl collection.
Music by Anton Kubikov, Federsen, El Choop, Soultek, Van Bonn and others.

The interactive comic takes place in ten thematic episodes (SL20–SL29), taking the form of an audio performance. The story recitation with musical accompaniment opens the first season of the sci-fi novel about the adventures of space travelers.

Welcome to the next episode of our podcast, the guest of which was the progressive musician and DJ from Yekaterinburg Genning. The exclusive vinyl mix includes compositions by Floppy Sounds, Eddie Richards, Audio Soul Project, 16B and Rafael Gomez.

Our next episode of the podcast features an amazing mix from Chris Kelly (Federsen), which includes tracks by such authors as Subset, Teluric, Altone, Kooscha and Joseph S. Joyce. Most recently, his original "Ataraxia" EP was released on spclnch. Excellent work from the master of the musical craft you can listen here: bit.ly/2LMg62o

We are glad to welcome again our friend from Ukraine M-Eject with his amazing music selection.
Featuring tracks by Heavenchord, Aspect., Basicnoise, Roman Ridder, Bioroot and various others.

This beautiful mix was recorded by the guys from Quadrant Soundscape - deep, measured and neat, all the way we love it. Enjoy listening.
Featuring music by Francisco Aguado, Havantepe, Roger Gerressen, Basicnoise, Markus Masuhr and various others.

The mix for our next episode was recorded by Giriu Dvasios (Evaldas Azbukauskas), consisting exclusively of the Cold Tear Records collection.
Featuring music by Echo Delta, Special Zip, Vejopatis, Heavenchord, Mikael Delta and various others.

A special mix compilation consisting of tracks released exclusively on spclnch.
Featuring music from Basicnoise, Kooscha, Altone, Upwellings, Subset and various others.
You can find all the tracks on our Bandcamp: https://bit.ly/2HwDiiS

The mix for the next series was recorded for us by airkey (Roman Kukharenko), it turned out to be high-quality and tasteful, have a nice trip.
Featuring music from Ochu Laross, Andrey Djackonda, Del Fonda, Scott Jaye, Prajesku and various others.
The guest of our next episode needs no introduction. Anton Kubikov with a fresh selection of deep & dub tracks from such authors as Rhauder, Havantepe, Grad_U, Altitude and many others.

The mix for our next series was prepared by British DJ T. Fitzgerald (aka Tom Clarke), a member of the creative association We Are FTR. A great selection from his personal collection, vinyl only.
Featuring music from Echoton, Clovis, Dubsons, Zefzeed, Mihigh & Lizz and various others.

Our Dutch friend Monosphere (aka Jeroen Smulders), the founder of the concept label Deep Electronics, has put together and recorded an amazing mix consisting of compositions by famous authors in the best traditions of the genre.
Featuring music from Heavenchord, Idealist, David Hausdorf, BDtom, Schulz Audio and various others.

A mix from our German friend Matthias Lindner, owner of the amazing vinyl label YARN Records, which releases atmospheric hypnotic minimal from talented artists. We go on a journey through the mysterious corners of dub techno.
Featuring music from Anton Kubikov, Biodub, Toki Fuko, Ion Ludwig, Roger Gerressen and various others.

"Art washes away from the soul the dust of everyday life."
Featuring music from Luigi Tozzi, Joeski, Eva Be, Denney & James Dexter, DkA and various others.

"I want everything to be perfect, even if it's internal details. A good carpenter will not take bad planks for the back of a cabinet, though no one will ever see it."
Featuring music from Zefzeed, Mariin, Artur Nikolaev, Loxique, G76 and various others.

A good day starts with a healthy breakfast and delicious music.
Featuring music from Yaleesa Hall x Malin Genie, Tomas Rubeck, Dilated Pupils, Beat Pharmacy, Luigi Tozzi and various others.

Drifting.Dubs returns with a new mix of perfectly selected tracks. As always delicious, neat and high-quality.
Featuring music from Marx Trukker, Loopdeville, Robert Drewek, Clark Davis, Adjustment Bureau and various others.

Cold tenderness with notes of alienation, time slows down. You transcend the doubts of the past and the certainty of the present, soul and mind in perfect harmony...
Featuring music from Monomood, Stephen Brown, Yagya, Deepchord, Federsen and various others.

An amazing deep dubby mix was recorded for us by Argonaut (Péter Jász), co-owner of the negyednégy music platform. Everything is as we like, classy and intelligent. Stay at home, listen to good music and don't get sick.
Featuring music from Federsen, STL, Ben Buitendijk, Resoe, Teluric and various others.

A mix of conceptual experimental electronics from Drifted. Fresh, classy and modern.
Featuring music from SZTVO, Toma Kami, VRAC, Giammarco Orsini, Burial and various others.

The dark mystical mix was prepared for us by French DJ and producer Quentin Michel aka Kød.
Featuring music from Ohm & Kvadrant, Ohrwert, Markus Suckut, Stewart Walker, BLNDR and various others.

"I have simple tastes. I am always satisfied with the best."
Featuring music from Gathaspar, Lisière Collectif, Steve O'Sullivan, Roger Gerressen, Malin Genie & Per Hammar and various others.

A portion of melancholy from Marcibagoly, consisting of original author's music, as well as works from Purl & Sinius, Docetism, Amanita Phalloides & Heavenchord, Whitewildbear, AtmÃ¸sphÃ¤re and other interesting musicians in the ambient genre. Last summer we released his EP called "Tales From Flowers", which harmoniously intertwines romance, beauty and true love.

Neat and cheerful vibe from our St. Petersburg friend Alexander Kopshev, consisting of new music and not only such labels as Irenic, Alter Hour, Rawax, Contemporan and others. In July 2019, a joint release by Kpsh and Romanian Alex Sfetcu titled "Aquanaut / Proud Wanderer" was released on spclnch, becoming a successful collaboration of artists with similar views on minimal house.
Featuring music from Luna Ludmila, Olivian Nour, iO (Mulen), VincentIulian, Nathan Paul and various others.

One of our residents Kooscha, an Australian DJ and producer, recorded a fresh exclusively vinyl mix for the spclnch podcast series. Recall that his release "Reflections", elegant, soft and at the same time dynamic, was the beginning of our history, and his remix of the track of the magnificent Upwellings "Illusory Fog" was part of the first vinyl released in a limited edition.
Featuring music from Malin Genie & Selidos, Arkajo, Tripmastaz, Venda, Mihigh and various others.

"What are the most characteristic qualities of extroverts? They are energized by the outside world - by actions, people, places and things... Long periods of inactivity, inner contemplation, or loneliness, or communication with only one person deprive them of the sense of meaning of life..."
Featuring music from Mariano Mateljan, Minube & Andrey Djackonda, Paolo Rocco & Lessi S, Premiesku, The Mountain People and various others.

"First the vision - then its material embodiment. First thought - then purposeful movement on the only path to the chosen goal. Can one have any meaning without the other? Is it not a vice to desire something and to do nothing, or to act without a purpose?"
Featuring music from Markus Homm, Teluric, Roger Gerressen, Room323, Steve O'Sullivan and various others.

"Taste, in its true meaning, is a harmony of experience, development and sensitivity to the beautiful."
Featuring music from Grad_U, Ini, Julian Perez, Altitude, Per Hammar and various others.

"The modern world does not need hatred, it needs goodwill, it needs agreement, cooperation and a much kinder moral climate; I think that even a little of the most ordinary love and cordiality can still work wonders."
Featuring music from ulises, Thommie G, Ameli Paul & JPattersson, Ali Kuru, kalupke and various others.

"Any kind of happiness is very personal. The greatest moments in our lives are very intimate, internally motivated and untouchable. What we refuse to share with anyone is sacred and precious to us. But now we are taught that we need to put everything personal on public display and let everyone grope."
Featuring music from Christopher Ledger, Janus Rasmussen, Ryan Davis, Super Flu, Stimming and various others.

"It's so ordinary when everyone understands you."
Featuring music from Toman, Orbit & Belogurov, Reyam, Djoko, Cateran and various others.

"It's a huge difference - to hear a sound or feel it. I felt the ocean, clouds, people, music. In my heart was unbearable pleasant pain, which was amplified from a favorite melody or just smile. I couldn't think about anything. I felt like I was seeing the world for the first time."

This live was recorded by Vincent Raude at the Dimensions festival in Croatia in 2018. Depth, space, dynamics, stunning dialogue and interaction of musical parties, minimalism.
By the way, on october 17 on spclnch will be released an EP from Upwellings under the title «Illusory Fog». The release will be available digitally as well as on limited edition vinyl (pre-order on Bandcamp: bit.ly/2ANDLGk).

"Never ask anyone. Especially about your work. Don't you know what you want? How can you live without knowing it?"
Featuring music from Alci, Heerd, Silat Beksi, Maik Yells, Christopher Ledger and various others. Enjoy!

"Every morning in Africa a gazelle wakes up. She must run faster than a lion, or die. Every morning in Africa a lion wakes up. He must run faster than a gazelle or he will starve to death. It doesn't matter if you're a gazelle or a lion. When the sun comes up, you gotta run."
Featuring music from Amorf, Cerec, Herck, Nick Beringer, Spiritual and various others. Enjoy!

"In this age of mass production from a huge range of products you can always find something for yourself. Try to understand your characteristics and remember that individuality and eccentricity are different concepts."
Featuring music from Swayzak, Roger Gerressen, Ion Ludwig, STL, Di Barsotti and various others. Enjoy!

"Music is difficult to understand rationally. Most listeners perceive music through emotions and will agree that it is abstract. Hardly anyone will undertake to translate music into the language of words - you just need to listen."
Featuring music from Ian R, Kpsh, Vern, Malbo, Yaroslav Lenzyak and various others. Enjoy!

"The first and probably the most important step in the development of style and taste is to learn to trust your own opinion."
Featuring music from Eddie Richards, Archie Hamilton, Fresh And Low, Escape Artist, Superlova and various others. Enjoy!

"In our time, when everywhere triumphant mediocrity, all significant, all true should swim or aloof or against the flow."
Featuring music from Giriu Dvasios, Tender H, Space Scavengers, SoulSonic, Monodisc and various others. Enjoy!
Mixed by Giriu Dvasios.

"With enthusiasm, you can achieve anything. Enthusiasm is the brilliance of your eyes, the swiftness of your gait, the strength of your handshake, the irresistible rush of energy and will to bring your ideas to life. Enthusiasm is the cornerstone of all progress! Only with it is success possible. Without it, you have only opportunities."
Featuring music from Alci, VincentIulian, Ben Rau, Nicolas Duvoisin & Borgo, Pierre C and various others. Enjoy!

"The best advertising of any product is its quality."
Featuring music from Anton Kubikov, Kpsh, Alex Sfetcu, Mikhail Kobzar, Dubphone and various others. Enjoy!"

"Empty your mind, be formless. Shapeless, like water. If you put water into a cup, it becomes the cup. You put water into a bottle and it becomes the bottle. You put it in a teapot it becomes the teapot. Now, water can flow or it can crash. Be water, my friend."
Featuring music from Dragomir, Macarie, La.Ma, Aleksandar Grum, Triptil and various others. Enjoy!

"And then, let's be honest: how long can you watch the sunset? And who would want to see the sunset lasted forever? And who needs eternal warmth? Who needs eternal flavor? After all, you get used to all this and just stop noticing. It's good to watch the sunset for a minute or two. And then you want something else. That's how a man works."
Featuring music from Marcibagoly, Goran Geto, Alex Sfetcu, Dublicator, Pacific Coliseum and various others. Enjoy!

"Listen to honest music, do not get fooled by stereotypes and fashion. Listen to your heart and be yourself!"
Featuring music from Ochu Laross, Lee Burton, Diego Krause, Giacomo Pellegrino, Dragutesku and various others. Enjoy!

"People have one wonderful flaw - we are unable to make perfect copies. It is because we cannot completely copy our heroes that we find our own life. This is how we evolve."
Featuring music from Tender H, Heavenchord, Silver Ash, Dub Taylor, Biodub and various others. Enjoy!

"I want you to stop looking outside yourself and listen to what's inside you. People are afraid of what's inside, and that's the only place they can find what they need."
Featuring music from Marcibagoly, Basicnoise, R.Hz, Heavenchord, Kirill Torno and various others. Enjoy!

"For music in general is very important, where and how you listen to it... And anyway, a proper, appropriate music all that you do, you will do well and with pleasure."
Featuring music from Andrea Ferlin & Luc Ringseisen, Katie Drover, Verrina & Ventura, Romar, Sakdat & Balaur and various others. Vinyl only, enjoy!

"It is often a vinyl sound that regularly dials lists of bestsellers in the store and is designed to be listened to for long periods of time."
Featuring music from Petre Inspirescu, Venda, Cleymoore, Kaitaro, Clarkent and various others. Enjoy!

"It is necessary to understand that history is not only dates and places, not only names in dusty textbooks or exhibits in museums, it is a choice that we make. Each of us."
Featuring music from John Tejada, Monteki, Prodot, Dot, Shimammo and various others. Enjoy!

"To be happy, you need to constantly be in a state of love with something. With music, with literature, with today's day, with life."
Featuring music from Tripsolate & Redundaent, Planetary Secrets, Matthias Haiker, Zoltan Ban, Giriu Dvasios and various others. Enjoy!

"Minimalism should not be perceived as the absence or lack of something. Quite the contrary, minimalism is the presence of space and air, freedom and everything we need most. A space for thoughts, space for creativity. This is the beauty of minimalism."
Featuring music from joergmueller, Modd, Drifting.Dubs, Pablo Bolivar & Dactilar, Basicnoise and various others. Enjoy!

"Real culture, Culture with a capital letter, such as music, literature, common sense and love of knowledge, is born in our heart, imagination and mind."
Featuring music from Ema Remedi, Sakro, Fabe, Jorge Savoretti, Claro Intelecto and various others. Enjoy!

"This is a leisurely story about good and pleasant moments that you want to live again and again, enjoying and forgetting about everything. Here you stand on the shore and feel the salty smell of the wind that blows from the sea. You're here, you're now, you're free, you're happy. What could be better?"
Featuring music from Biosphere, Heavenchord, Solar Fields, Jason van Wyk, State Azure and various others. Enjoy!

The next episode was recorded by Nicolas Barnes, a DJ and producer from Riga, who has a good taste, a sense of style and a great love for his musical work. A seasoned, minimalistic and clean mix, under the vibration of which you can perfectly move or do what you love.
Featuring music from Ki.Mi., Dubfound, Vendi, Silat Beksi, Rhymos and various others. Enjoy!

Kooscha, a producer and DJ from Australia's largest and first city, Sydney, opens a series of podcasts about intelligent electronic music with his fresh, danceable, carefully selected and mixed musical journey.
Featuring music from Star_Dub, Alma, Kooscha, Raynes, Petter Preston and various others. Enjoy!

chooseYourColor.description: The natural course of any sequence is to experience rebirth at a certain point and tend to improve thanks to its character. One of such improvements is assigned the role of a guide to another dimension. Implicating a change of positions, the soothing pads shape the basis for realising artistic images. A soft straight kick sows completeness and regularity in the simplicity of explanations.

The string of temperamental rhythms swirls in a whirlpool of laconic micro-abstractions. The invigorating synthesizer pieces are flashing with colorful slides and liberating one by the attractiveness of their dance. The cool Munich house pleases with the aroma of nostalgia, which has a hint of musical spices.

Stretched as a purposely slowed-down pulse that highlights the hissing of a storage device. This listening artefact recreates a vivid impression of the friction of the film passing through a magnetic head. The plastic textures fuse the worlds of tactile perception and life-giving digital abundance.

A night walk along the Baltic Sea coast awakens a pagan fear of the elements. The wavering amber wind penetrates the smoldering body and makes it burn even brighter. The cozy alley smells of rye dough and smoked lamprey, and the neon-pink backlight is filled with warm oil. Everyone will find peace here.

Eccentric jazz improvisations ignite the lost hopes. The evening promenade, the bridges of the Seine and even the underground ossuary are all full of innocence. You can see a mystery in everything. With an unhurried gait, the unity of contradictions is walking barefoot on cobblestone sidewalks.

The dark legacy of the bygone empire is not only the fall of Constantinople and the greed of the ruling nobility. It's more than that. The collision of echoes of the past and the technologies of the present creates a special rhythmic geometry. Professional sound engineering skills bring field recordings to a new aesthetic level. Modern antiquity is blowing from the shores of foggy Albion.

The spiritistic mosaic breaks up into many episodes, whirls around like scattered phantom rearrangements and then develops ornate patterns once again. The textural metamorphoses of the mysterious detective from the Ancient Capital harmoniously evolve inside the monochrome percussion system.

The faded pictures show an assertive breakbeat, which is gushing with drum beats and is deifying love. The energy of beauty, penetrated by the dancefloor passion, can be heard from the fascinating sidewalks of Khreshchatyk. The masterpiece concept is painted with rich spring colors and an atmosphere of freedom.

The crystal-clear plot is enriched by the dawning Australian sun. Score sketches with shy dreams and soft freshness are luring into the open arms of warming therapy. A great reason for cultivating peace and expanding your musical horizons.

And here's Thomas. Driven by the desire for orderliness, he discovers borderline states of the tangible and the ghostly, the explicit and the secret, the habitual and the abstract. The mysterious forms are tightly intertwined with the extraterrestrial predilections, creating an aura of inexplicability.

A native of the country of countless lakes, villages and high-altitude Alps goes on a full-length sci-fi voyage. A platform arcade game doesn't experience technical limitations, belonging to the same dimension as the mystery of the third planet. The advanced sound design offers an interesting physical model within the stereo emulation in a form of a set of difficulty levels and modes. Start!

Joey Rösler honors the high standards of the German music industry, carefully replicating them in his style. The austerity of the outlines conceals the harmony of the keyboard, the warmth of the morning wind and the contemplation of the centuries-old cypresses. Expressively bustling life is reflected in the color interpretation from the Ruhr region.

The airy house music is carried around by means of intoxicating embraces. Colorful hi-hats and a delicate bassline add volume to the sound constructions. How to distinguish Bordeaux from Burgundy? Order a glass of red!

A fresh shade appeared in the metaphysical palette — ethereal ambient noise from Pittsburgh. A monumental background mantra oozes through the buzzing swarm of everyday noise, symbolizing the beauty of endless labors and the sound of inner vocation.

description.article:
"Spacelunch" (short. spclnch) is a Dutch electronic music label with an emphasis on the dub sound founded in Minsk in 2019 by Thomas Carmody. The key ethical principles are an individual approach and a careful selection which allows you to get the best possible from the communication with artists. 

The concept of releases is dedicated to a fantastic multimedia universe. The space adventures of Spacelunch and Cat unfold in episodes of an interactive musical comic. Each of them has an original script, and they are connected by a consistent storyline.

description.title: Main characters
description.article:
Spacelunch is a brilliant scientist, a stylish merry fellow and a music lover. An adventurer with a quick mind and lightning-fast analytics; a gambler and a sore loser who has a constant thirst for discoveries, which is why he and his partener often get into trouble. He doesn't remember the last time he was on his home planet or if he has ever been there at all. He travels on an aircraft with a warp engine.

Cat is Spacelunch's once-beloved pet, accidentally endowed with human intelligence and the ability to speak in one of his experiments. In critical situations, he is skeptical, grumpy, but shows ingenuity and courage. Has a great command of a service blaster.

Minimal-antagonist is a fiend of hopeless darkness in the guise of a giant cuttlefish. The envious, unscrupulous and cruel creator of the aerospace corporation. He is able to summon shadow phantoms, to connect to someone else's consciousness and to control it. The phenomenal regeneration allows him to remain virtually invulnerable. He tries to stop sound stalkers in every possible way, intends to destroy anyone who comes close to solving the mysteries of the musical universe.

The Queen of Smorings is the leader of the rebel movement and the guardian of friendly people who have been under the yoke of invaders for many years. Empathic, sensitive, at the same time imperious, unshakable and wise in decisions. She lives in a valley on one of the stars of the Alpha Centauri system, has high extrasensory sensitivity.

description.title: Universe and plot
description.article:
The mechanics of the universe is based on basic knowledge about the cosmos, but first of all describes sound phenomena that interact directly with the listener. They are a catalyst for the events taking place and they also explain the nature of the development of atypical processes. 

The narrative originates on the margins of the space-time continuum. The main characters hunt for rare artifacts in different dimensions and star systems. One of the trips presents an unpleasant surprise and their space gadget is sucked into a black hole. From now on, nothing goes according to their plan and things take an unexpected turn...
